  "prompt": "What are the best songs of 2016?",
  "response": "The \"best\" songs of 2016 can be subjective and depend on personal taste, genre preferences, and cultural impact. However, here are some of the most popular and critically acclaimed songs from 2016, based on charts, awards, and cultural influence:\n\n### Pop/Dance:\n1. **\"Formation\"** - Beyonc\u00e9  \n2. **\"Work\"** - Rihanna ft. Drake  \n3. **\"Closer\"** - The Chainsmokers ft. Halsey  \n4. **\"Cheap Thrills\"** - Sia ft. Sean Paul  \n5. **\"Starboy\"** - The Weeknd ft. Daft Punk  \n\n### Hip-Hop/R&B:\n1. **\"One Dance\"** - Drake ft. Wizkid & Kyla  \n2. **\"Broccoli\"** - DRAM ft. Lil Yachty  \n3. **\"Black Beatles\"** - Rae Sremmurd ft. Gucci Mane  \n4. **\"Panda\"** - Desiigner  \n\n### Rock/Alternative:\n1. **\"Heathens\"** - Twenty One Pilots  \n2. **\"Ride\"** - Twenty One Pilots  \n3. **\"Dark Necessities\"** - Red Hot Chili Peppers  \n\n### Country:\n1. **\"H.O.L.Y.\"** - Florida Georgia Line  \n2. **\"Church Bells\"** - Carrie Underwood  \n\n### Other Notable Tracks:\n1. **\"Can't Stop the Feeling!\"** - Justin Timberlake  \n2. **\"This Is What You Came For\"** - Calvin Harris ft. Rihanna  \n3. **\"Cold Water\"** - Major Lazer ft. Justin Bieber & M\u00d8  \n4. **\"All We Know\"** - The Chainsmokers ft. Phoebe Ryan  \n\nThese songs dominated charts, streaming platforms, and radio airplay throughout 2016, and many of them remain iconic today. Let me know if you'd like more recommendations or insights!",
